STANDARD OPERATING CONDITIONS
1. INTRODUCTORY STATEMENT
Except where expressly stated otherwise, this statement of General Terms and Standard Operating Condition (hereinafter “statement”) shall apply to all natural gas storage services rendered by Lee 8 Storage Partnership (“Lee 8”) under any storage service contract, including, but not limited to, firm and interruptible services.
2. DEFINITIONS The following terms as used in this statement shall have the meaning or definitions set forth below (such definitions to e equally applicable to the singular and the plural forms of the terms defined):
2.01 “Billed Month” shall have meaning assigned in Section 12.
2.02 “British Thermal Unit (Btu)” shall mean the amount of heat required to raise the temperature of one (1) avoirdupois pound of pure water from fifty-eight and one-half degrees Fahrenheit (58.5º F) to fifty-nine and one-half degrees Fahrenheit (59.5º F) under standard conditions.
2.03 “Contract” shall mean a Gas storage contract between Lee 8 and Customer.
2.04 “Cushion Gas” shall mean the gas required to remain in the storage reservoir to protect the reservoir’s integrity. Customer shall make all arrangements necessary to provide the quantity of cushion gas necessary to support Customer’s Contract MSQ with Lee 8.
2.05 “Customer” shall mean the party that has executed a Contract with Lee 8 and holds all lawful rights and title to the natural gas that is being stored.
2.06 “Day” shall mean a period of twenty-four (24) consecutive hours beginning and ending at 9:00 A.M. central time. The reference date for any Day shall be the date of the beginning of such Day.
2.07 “FERC or Commission” shall mean the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission or any successor agency.
2.08 “Firm Service” shall mean the use of the Storage Facilities to the extent to the maximum injection, withdrawal, and storage capacities reserved for use by a Customer under a Contract between such Customer and Lee 8 which use shall not be subject to and will not become subject to any other claim by person as to the use of that portion of the storage Facilities reserved for such Customer.
2.09 “Fuel Gas” shall mean the incremental amount of Gas (for compressor fuel) that Customer shall deliver to Lee 8 in excess of Customer’s injection and withdrawal volumes.
2.10 “Gas” shall mean natural Gas in its natural state, produced from wells, including casinghead Gas produced with crude oil, natural Gas from Gas wells, vaporized liquefied natural Gas, and residue Gas resulting from processing both casinghead gas and Gas well Gas, which equals or exceeds the minimum quality specifications set forth in Section 8 hereof.
2.11 “Gas Storage Inventory Account” shall mean the quantity of working Gas stored in the Storage Facilities by Lee 8 for Customer’s account.
2.12 “Injection Fee” shall mean the fee paid by Customer to Lee 8 for the injection of Gas into the storage Facilities.
2.13 “Injection and Withdrawal Capacity” shall mean the maximum quantity of Gas that Lee 8 may physically receive from all Customers and inject into, or withdraw from, the Storage Facilities each Day.
2.14 “Interruptible Service” shall mean the use of the Storage Facilities is subject to interruption at any time by Lee 8 in order to accommodate the use of the Storage Facilities, or any part thereof, by (i) any Firm Service Customer, or (ii) any Interruptible Service Customer with a higher priority claim to the Storage Facilities.
2.15 “MSQ” or “Maximum Storage Quantity” shall mean the maximum quantity of Gas which Customer may have in its Gas Storage Inventory Account at any time under the terms of the Customer’s Contract.
2.16 “Mcf” shall mean one thousand (1,000) cubic feet at a pressure of fourteen and sixty-five hundredths (14.65) psia and at a temperature of sixty degrees Fahrenheit (60º F), with correction for deviation from Boyle's Law.
2.17 “MDIQ” or “Maximum Daily Injection Quantity” shall mean the aggregate maximum quantity of Gas that Customer may nominate and deliver and that Lee 8 shall receive at the Point(s) of Receipt for injection into the Storage Facilities each Day at constant hourly rates of flow over the course of such Day; provided that, injections at other than uniform rates of flow shall be governed by the Contract; and provided further, a Customer's MDIQ shall be subject to daily adjustments as Lee 8, in the exercise of its reasonable discretion, may determine are necessary for the safe and efficient operation of Storage Facilities.
2.18 “MDWQ” or “Maximum Daily Withdrawal Quantity” shall mean the aggregate maximum quantity of Gas that Customer may nominate and that Lee 8 will withdraw from the Storage Facilities and tender to Customer at the Point(s) of Delivery each Day at constant hourly rates of flow over the course of such Day; provided that, withdrawals at other than uniform rates of flow shall be governed by the Contract; and provided further a customer's MDWQ shall be subject to daily adjustments as Lee 8, in the exercise of its reasonable discretion, may determine are necessary for the safe and efficient operation of the Storage Facilities.
2.19 “Metering Facilities” shall mean the facilities referenced in Section 11.
2.20 “MMBtu” shall mean 1,000,000 Btu.
2.21 "Month” shall mean that period of time beginning at 9:00 A.M. central time on the first Day of a calendar month and ending at 9:00 A.M. central time on the first Day of the following calendar month.
2.22 “Nomination Procedures” shall mean the procedures specified in Sections 5 and 6 pursuant to which Customer shall nominate Gas for injection into, or withdrawal from, the Storage Facilities.
2.23 “Point(s) of Delivery” shall mean the point(s) specified in Customer's Contract, at which Lee 8 shall deliver Gas to Customer from the Storage Facilities.
2.24 “Point(s) of Receipt” shall mean the point(s) specified in Customer's Contract, at which Lee 8 shall receive Gas from Customer for injection into the Storage Facilities.
2.25 “Potential Customer” shall mean any person that desires to execute a Contract with Lee 8.
2.26 “psia” shall mean pounds per square inch absolute.
2.27 “psig” shall mean pounds per square inch gauge.
2.28 “Storage Capacity” shall mean the Volume equivalent to the maximum quantity of working Gas, which may be stored by all Customers in the Storage Facilities at a given time.
2.29 “Storage Facilities” shall mean the underground natural Gas storage reservoirs and related building, improvements, pipelines, surface fixtures and equipment that are owned and/or controlled by Lee 8.
2.30 “Total Storage Reservation Fee” shall mean the fee paid by Customer to Lee 8 for the purpose of reserving capacity in the Storage Facilities.
2.31 “Total Storage Service” shall mean the MDWQ, the MDIQ, and the MSQ specified in Customer's Contract.
2.32 “Transporter(s)” shall mean a third-party transporter designated by Customer to deliver Gas to the Point(s) of Receipt or to receive Gas at the Point(s) of Delivery.
2.33 “Volume” shall mean a quantity of Gas measured or expressed in MMBtu’s.
2.34 “Withdrawal Fee” shall mean the fee paid by Customer to Lee 8 for the withdrawal of Gas from the Storage Facilities.
3. REQUEST FOR STORAGE SERVICE
3.1 Execution of Contracts. Each Customer shall be required to execute a service contract for storage service no later than thirty (30) consecutive days following the date Lee 8 tenders a Contract to Potential Customers.
3.2 Requests. Any Potential Customer wishing to obtain storage services from Lee 8 shall submit in writing to Lee 8 a request for storage service in a form designed by Lee 8. Such request may be delivered in person or submitted by United States mail, overnight courier service, or facsimile transmission (fax). Lee 8 shall evaluate and respond to Potential Customer's request within ten (10) business Days of its receipt. If Lee 8 and Potential Customer mutually agree to the rates that Potential Customer will pay for storage service, Lee 8 shall, subject to execution of a Contract, endeavor to provide service within the time specified in the written request. A Potential Customer's request for storage service shall be considered complete only if the information specified in Sections 3.3 and 3.4 is provided in writing.
Request for Service may be sent to:
Lee 8 Storage Partnership Attn: Contract Administration P.O. Box 4967 Houston, TX 77210-4967
3.3 Information Requirements. A request for service shall include the following information:
3.3.1 The Potential Customer's name, address, representative and telephone number.
3.3.2 A statement of whether Potential Customer is a local natural gas distribution company (LDC), an intrastate pipeline company, an interstate pipeline company, marketer/broker, producer, end user or other type of entity (which other entity must be described).
3.3.3 Volume and type of service requested, whether Firm or Interruptible for each of the following:
3.3.3.1 Maximum Storage Quantity (stated in MMBtu).
3.3.3.2 Maximum Daily Withdrawal Quantity (stated in MMBtu/Day) and at which Point(s) of Delivery.
3.3.3.3 Maximum Daily Injection Quantity (stated in MMBtu/Day) and at which Point(s) of Receipt.
3.3.4 Term of service, including the date service is requested to commence and the date service is requested to terminate.
3.3.5 Evidence of creditworthiness. Acceptance of a storage service request is contingent upon a satisfactory credit appraisal by Lee 8. Such credit appraisal must meet the following criteria:
3.3.5.1 Potential Customer shall provide (a) current financial statements, annual reports, 10-K reports and other filings with regulatory agencies; (b) a list of all corporate affiliates, parent companies and subsidiaries; and (c) any reports from credit reporting agencies, which are available. Lee 8 shall apply consistent evaluation practices to determine the acceptability of the Potential Customer's overall financial condition, working capital, and profitability trends.
3.3.5.2 A bank reference and at least two trade references must be provided by a Potential Customer. The results of reference checks and any credit reports must show that Potential Customer's obligations are being paid on a prompt basis.
3.3.5.3 A Potential Customer must not be operating under any chapter of the bankruptcy laws and must not be subject to liquidation or debt reduction procedures under the state laws, such as an assignment for the benefit of creditors, or any informal creditors' committee agreement. An exception can be made for a Potential Customer who is a debtor in possession operating under Chapter XI of the Federal Bankruptcy Act but only with adequate assurances that billings will be paid promptly as cost of administration under the federal court's jurisdiction.
3.3.5.4 A Potential Customer must not be subject to the uncertainty of pending liquidation or regulatory proceedings in state or federal courts which could cause a substantial deterioration in its financial condition, which could cause a condition of insolvency, or which could impair the ability of the Potential Customer to continue to exist as an ongoing business entity.
3.3.5.5 If a Potential Customer has an ongoing business relationship with Lee 8, no delinquent balances shall be consistently outstanding for natural gas storage services provided previously by Lee 8. Potential Customer shall have paid its account for past periods according to established contract terms, not having made deductions or withheld payment not authorized by contract.
3.3.5.6 No significant collection lawsuits or judgments shall be outstanding which would seriously reflect upon the Potential Customer's ability to remain solvent.
3.3.5.7 If a Potential Customer fails to satisfy the credit criteria or subsequently during the term of the service agreement no longer satisfies the credit criteria, such Potential Customer may still obtain storage service to Lee 8 if it elects one of the following options: (i) a standby irrevocable letter of credit drawn upon a bank acceptable to Lee 8 in an amount acceptable to Lee 8; (ii) a security interest in collateral provided by the Potential Customer found to be satisfactory to Lee 8; or (iii) guarantee of performance of all obligations owed to Lee 8 by a person or entity which does satisfy the credit appraisal.
3.4 Subsequent Information
3.4.1 If any of the events or actions described in Sections 3.4.5.3, 3.4.5.4, and 3.4.5.6 above, shall be initiated or imposed during the term of service under a Contract, Customer shall provide notification to Lee 8 within two (2) business Days of any such initiated or imposed event or action. Customer shall also promptly provide such additional Customer credit information as may be reasonably required by Lee 8, at any time during the term of service under a Contract, to determine Customer's creditworthiness.
3.4.2 After receipt of a request for service, Lee 8 may require that a Potential Customer furnish additional information as a prerequisite to Lee 8 offering to execute a Contract with the Potential Customer. Such information may include proof of the Potential Customer's lawful right and title to cause the Gas to be delivered to Lee 8 for storage and of the Potential Customer's contractual or physical ability to cause such Gas to be delivered to and received from Lee 8.
3.5 Request Validity. If Lee 8 has tendered a Contract for execution to a Potential Customer and Potential Customer fails to execute the Contract as tendered within thirty (30) consecutive days from the date the Contract has been tendered by Lee 8, Lee 8 may consider Potential Customer's service request void. For Firm service, Lee 8 will not be required to tender a Contract to a Potential Customer for execution that relates to requests for service for which Lee 8 does not have sufficient available Firm capacity, injection or withdrawal capabilities.
3.6 Customer’s Performance. Customer is required to provide to Lee 8 (1) the state of the consumption for the Gas that is to be withdrawn from storage and (2) such other information, if required, in order for Lee 8 to comply with any FERC reporting or other requirements.
3.7 Complaints. In the event that a Customer or Potential Customer has a complaint relative to storage service, the Customer or Potential Customer shall provide a description of the complaint, verbally or in writing, including the identification of the storage service request (if applicable), and communicate it to:
Lee 8 Storage Partnership Attn: Customer Service P.O. Box 4967 Houston, TX 77210-4967
Lee 8 will verbally respond initially within seventy-two (72) hours, or three (3) business Days, whichever is later, from the day of receipt of a complaint. Lee 8 shall respond in writing within forty-five (45) Days of receipt of the complaint advising Customer or a Potential Customer of the disposition of the complaint.
3.8 Information.
3.8.1 Any person may request information by contacting Lee 8 at the following:
Lee 8 Storage Partnership Attn: Customer Service P.O. Box 4967 Houston, TX 77210-4967
3.8.2 Each Customer will be provided with a list of phone numbers for Lee 8's dispatch and control personnel, who are on-call 24-hours a Day.
3.8.3 Each Customer will provide to Lee 8 a list of phone numbers of Customer's personnel who will be available, including those on a 24-hours a Day basis.
4. PRIORITY AND INTERRUPTION OF SERVICE
4.1 Priority of Service. Any Customer executing a storage service contract with Lee 8 shall be entitled to the injection, storage and withdrawal of Gas, subject to the availability of storage capacity, injection and deliverability in the following order of declining priority:
4.1.1 Firm services pursuant to Section 4.2 below.
4.1.2 Interruptible services pursuant to Section 4.3 below.
4.2 Interruptible Services. Contracts relating to Interruptible service obligations shall have priority as follows:
4.2.1 The order of priority relating to storage service requests under Interruptible service shall be by the average daily Total Storage Reservation Fee agreed to by Lee 8 and Customer, with the highest charge calculated on a daily basis given highest priority.
4.2.2 Should two or more Interruptible Customers have the same priority, capacity will be allocated on a pro rata basis to each Customer.
4.3 Interruption.
4.3.1 If on any Day, due to any cause whatsoever, Lee 8's capability to receive or deliver volumes is impaired so that it, in its discretion, determines that it is unable to receive or deliver all the volumes which are scheduled, then interruption of storage service shall be made in the order of priority set forth in Section 4.1, where Customers having the lowest priority will be interrupted first. If Firm Service must be interrupted, interruption of storage service to Firm Customers shall be pro rata based on MSQ, MDIQ and/or MDWQ, as applicable. Interruption of storage service to Interruptible Customers shall be based on the storage service charges paid by Customer, with the lowest rate being interrupted first. Any Interruptible Service ties shall be interrupted in accordance with 4.3.
4.3.2 Lee 8 shall provide Customer as much advance notice of any interruption as is practicable under the circumstances. Such notice shall state the reduced volumes of Gas that Lee 8 estimates it will be able to inject or withdraw for Customer and the estimated duration of the interruption.
4.4 Interruption Liability. Lee 8 shall not be liable for any loss or damage to any person or property caused, in whole or in part, by any interruption of service, except to the extent caused solely by Lee 8's gross negligence or willful misconduct.
5. STORAGE OPERATIONS
5.1 Customer shall tender or cause to be tendered to Lee 8 at the Point(s) of Receipt any Gas which Customer desires to have injected into storage plus applicable Fuel Gas volumes. Lee 8 shall deliver or cause to be delivered Gas which Customer desires to be withdrawn from storage at the Point(s) of Delivery less Fuel Gas volumes.
5.2 Subject to the operating conditions of the Transporter(s) and the Storage Facilities, Lee 8 shall receive Gas for injection from Customer at the Point(s) of Receipt and deliver Gas to Customer at the Point(s) of Delivery as scheduled by Customer from time to time; provided that Lee 8 shall not be obligated to receive for injection any quantity of Gas if the injection of the same would cause the quantity of Gas stored for Customer's account to exceed Customer's Maximum Storage Quantity; nor shall Lee 8 be obligated at any time to deliver more Gas to Customer than either Customer's Maximum Daily Withdrawal Quantity or the Volume in Customer's Gas Storage Inventory Account.
6. SCHEDULING
6.1 During any Day when Customer desires Lee 8 to receive and inject Gas into, or to withdraw and deliver Gas from storage, Customer shall submit a nomination via fax, that includes but is not limited to the following information: volume, flow period, upstream transportation contract number(s) (for injections), downstream transportation contract number(s) (for withdrawals), Customer name and Contract number, the Customer's authorized employee name and telephone number, the type of service desired, the state of the consumption of Gas.
6.2 Customer shall make available and tender any Gas to be injected hereunder and receive and accept delivery, upon tender by Lee 8, of any Gas requested to be withdrawn from storage. Customer's Gas Storage Inventory Account shall be increased or decreased upon injection or withdrawal of Gas from storage, as applicable. Customer shall not (unless otherwise agreed by Lee 8) tender for injection, nor shall Lee 8 be obligated to receive Gas for injection, or to withdraw and deliver Gas from storage, on an hourly basis at rates of flow in excess of 1/24 of Customer's MDIQ or MDWQ, respectively.
6.3 On or before the 25th day of each month, Customer shall advise Lee 8, with written confirmation within 24 hours, of the daily quantity of gas, up to the Maximum Daily Injection Quantity, that will be received by Lee 8 during the following month, and/or daily quantity of gas, up to the Maximum Daily Withdrawal Quantity, that Customer will require Lee 8 to deliver during the following month. Customer may change this nomination upon 24 hours prior notice to Lee 8. Customer may also change this nomination upon less than 24 hours prior to Lee 8 subject to the determination, to be made by Lee 8 at its discretion, that such change will not jeopardize the operation of the Lee 8 Storage Field or service to Lee 8's other firm storage customers.
6.4 Changes in Nominations.
6.4.1 Customer shall notify Lee 8 at least twenty-four (24) hours in advance of any requested change in the daily or hourly rate of flow for injections or withdrawals of Gas pursuant to the schedule listed below.
6.4.2 Lee 8 may waive any part of the twenty-four (24) hour notice upon request if, in Lee 8's judgment, operating conditions permits such waiver and transportation(s) permit such action. Customer shall notify Lee 8 immediately of any circumstance which causes or will cause the deliveries to or receipts from Lee 8 to be different from those requested.
6.4.3 Nominations will be processed for scheduling in the order in which they are received by priority level as described in Section 4.1 of this Statement.
6.4.4 Notices provided in this Section 6 must be submitted in writing via fax. Customer shall provide notice of any changes in deliveries to or receipt from Lee 8 to all applicable Transporter(s) and shall be responsible for, and shall hold Lee 8 harmless from, any and all liabilities and expense resulting from any such changes.
6.4.5 Nominations to schedule Gas for the first Day of a prospective month must be submitted no later than the date and time allowed by the Transporter(s) for injections, and Transporter(s) for withdrawals, as indicated in the Transporter’s(s’) respective tariffs. Nominations received after these dates and times will be deemed "late" and will require that the Customer re-nominate for service to commence at a time accepted by Transporter(s).
6.5 Nomination Penalty. On any Day when Customer's actual confirmed receipt or deliveries differs from Customer nominations pursuant to Section 6.1 or 6.3, then Lee 8 shall penalize Customer and Customer shall pay Lee 8 the nomination penalty agreed to between Customer and Lee 8 as set out in Customer's Contract.
7. POINT(S) OF RECEIPT/DELIVERY
7.1 Point(s) of Receipt. Customer shall tender all Gas for injection into storage at the Point(s) of Receipt as specified in Customer's Contract. The quantity of Gas tendered by Customer to Lee 8 for injection into storage shall (i) not exceed at each Point(s) of Receipt the MDIQ for such Point plus the applicable Fuel Gas in effect from time to time, or (ii) not exceed at all Point(s) of Receipt the MDIQ plus applicable Fuel Gas in effect from time to time, without the consent of Lee 8.
7.2 Points(s) of Delivery. Lee 8 shall deliver all Gas withdrawn from storage to Customer at the Point(s) of Delivery as specified in Customer's Contact. The quantity of Gas delivered to Customer shall (i) not exceed at each Point(s) of Delivery the MDWQ for such Point plus the applicable Fuel Gas in effect from time to time, or (ii) not exceed the MDWQ at all Point(s) of Delivery plus the applicable Fuel Gas in effect from time to time, without the consent of Lee 8.
7.3 Transportation Guidelines. The Transporter(s) rules, guidelines, operational procedures and policies, they may be changed from time to time, shall define and control the manner in which Gas is delivered and received at the Point(s) of Delivery and Receipt. Lee 8 and Customer each agree to provide to the other, in as prompt a manner as reasonable, all information necessary to permit scheduling pursuant to such requirements. In addition, Lee 8 will not be required to begin injections or withdrawals for a Customer's account unless and until the data required for nominations, provided for in Section 6.1, have been confirmed by the applicable Transporter(s) to Lee 8's Gas dispatcher.
7.4 Transportation Imbalances. The event that Lee 8 or Customer delivers or causes to be delivered to Transporter(s) at the Point(s) of Receipt or Delivery a quantity of Gas not equal to the volume of Gas received or taken by Customer or Lee 8, a "Transportation Imbalance" may occur. Provided that Lee 8 has taken or delivered the quantity of Gas nominated by Customer and scheduled by Transporter(s), Customer shall be liable for all imbalances under its transportation agreement(s) with Transporter(s). Upon notification by Customer or Transporter(s) that a Transportation Imbalance exists because Lee 8 failed to deliver or receive the quantity of Gas nominated by Customer and scheduled by Transporter(s), Lee 8 will endeavor to correct the Transportation Imbalance subject to any restrictions imposed by Transporter(s). Customer agrees to use its best efforts to prevent or diminish any occurrences of imbalances.
7.5 Measurement. Customer and Lee 8 agree that the volumes of Gas delivered hereunder shall be measured by Lee 8 in accordance with the Transporter’s(s’) pipeline tariff, and, as such, may be allowed to fluctuate within the applicable measurement or flow tolerances on a daily and monthly basis.
7.6 Cost and Penalties. Customer shall hold Lee 8 harmless for all costs and -ties which and may be assessed by Transporter(s) under Customer's transportation agreement with Transporter(s). Customer and Lee 8 shall cooperate with each other and with the Transporter(s) to verify delivery and receipt of the volumes of Gas delivered hereunder.
7.7 Downstream and Upstream. Customer shall be responsible for transportation from the Point(s) of Delivery and payment of all transportation charges relating thereto. Customer shall be responsible for transportation to the Points(s) of Receipt and payment of all transportation charges relating thereto.
8. QUALITY 8.1 Specifications. The Gas delivered by either Lee 8 or Customer to the other hereunder shall meet the then current quality specifications of the Transporter(s) which receives or delivers such Gas at the Point(s) of Receipt or Delivery, as applicable.
8.2 Rejection of Gas. Either Lee 8 or Customer shall be entitled to reject any Gas tendered to it by the other which does not meet the minimum specifications of Section 8.1. Acceptance of such Gas does not constitute any waiver of Lee 8's right to refuse to accept similarly nonconforming Gas.
9. PRESSURE AND INJECTION/WITHDRAWAL RATES
9.1 Delivery Pressures. Lee 8 shall deliver Gas to Customer at pressures sufficient to enter the pipeline facilities at the Point(s) of Delivery against the operating pressures maintained by Transporter(s). Lee 8 shall not be required to deliver Gas at pressures in excess of those required by Transporter(s) or in excess of Transporter(s) maximum allowable operating pressure (MAOP), not to exceed 1,000 psig. Customer shall deliver or cause to be delivered to Lee 8 all Gas at the Point(s) of Receipt at such pressures as may exist from time to time in the Transporter(s) facilities at such points, but in no event shall Lee 8 be obligated to accept Gas at a pressure in excess of 1,000 psig or below 350 psig at the Point(s) of Receipt.
9.2 Injection and Withdrawal Rates. Lee 8 has designed the facilities required to inject and withdraw Gas from the storage reservoir based on "normal" operating pressures maintained by the Transporter(s) at the Point(s) of Receipt and Delivery with allowances for reasonable fluctuations. In the event that conditions on the Transporter(s) vary substantially from this, "normal" design condition coincident with high levels of Customer injection or withdrawal activity, Lee 8’s capability to receive or deliver the volumes set forth in its storage contracts may be impaired, and may cause an interruption in service. In such event, services will be allocated pursuant to Section 4. Customer agrees to indemnify and hold Lee 8 harmless for any lose caused by any such interruption in service. 10. TITLE AND RISK OF LOSS
10.1 Title to the natural gas stored by Lee 8 and delivered to Customer hereunder shall, at all times, be held by Customer; provided, however, that Lee 8 may, at its discretion and subject to all regulatory opinions and orders, waive such requirement, Customer warrants for itself its successors and assigns, that it will have at the time of delivery of Gas for storage hereunder good title. Customer warrants for itself, its successors and assigns, that the Gas it delivers hereunder shall be free and clear of all liens, encumbrances, or claims whatsoever; and that it will indemnify Lee 8 and save it harmless from all claims, suits, actions, damages, costs and expenses arising directly or indirectly from or with respect to the title to Gas tendered to Lee 8 hereunder.
10.2 Risk of Loss. As between Customer and Lee 8 Customer shall be in control and possession of the Gas prior to delivery to Lee 8 for injection at the Point(s) of Receipt and after redelivery by Lee 8 to Customer at the Point(s) of Delivery, and shall indemnify and hold Lee 8 harmless from any damage or injury caused thereby. Lee 8 shall be in control and possession of the Gas alter the receipt of the same for injection at the Point(s) of Receipt and until redelivery by Lee 8 to Customer at the Point(s) of Delivery, and shall indemnify and hold Customer harmless from any damage or injury caused thereby, except for damages and injuries caused by the sole negligence of Customer. The risk of loss for all Gas injected into, stored in and withdrawn from storage shall remain with Customer, and Lee 8 shall not be liable to Customer for any loss of Gas, except as may be occasioned due to the intentional or grossly negligent acts or omissions by Lee 8. Any losses of Gas, unless due to the intentional or grossly negligent acts or omissions of Lee 8, shall be shared proportionally by all Customers.
11. MEASUREMENT
The unit of volume for measurement of all quantities of Gas in terms of Mcf's and Btu's delivered to and received from storage hereunder shall be one (1) cubic foot of Gas at a base temperature of sixty degrees Fahrenheit (60º F) and at a pressure of 14.65 psia. All fundamental constants, observations, records, and procedures involved in determining and/or verifying the quantity and other characteristics of Gas delivered hereunder shall, unless; otherwise specified herein, be in accordance with the standards prescribed by the American Gas Association, as now and from time to time amended or supplemented. All measurements of Gas shall be determined by calculation into terms of such unit. All quantities given herein, unless expressly stated otherwise, are in terms of such unit. Notwithstanding the foregoing, it is agreed that, for all purposes, the Btu content of the Gas received and delivered by Lee 8 hereunder shall be measured on a dry basis.
Lee 8 shall install, maintain and operate, or cause to be installed, maintained and operated, the measurement facilities required hereunder. Said measurement facilities shall be so equipped with orifice meters, recording gauges, or other types of meters of standard make and design commonly acceptable in the industry, so as to accomplish, in Lee 8's judgment, the accurate measurement of Gas delivered hereunder. The retrieval of data, calibrating and adjustment of meters shall be done by Lee 8 or its agent.
12. BILLING AND PAYMENT
12.1 Monthly Statement. Except as otherwise provided herein, on or before the tenth (10th) calendar Day of each Month (“Issuing Month”). Lee 8 shall render to Customer a statement which sets forth the total charges for the services provided by Lee 8 to Customer in the preceding month (“Billed Month”).
12.2 Payment of Statements. Customer shall pay by electronic transfer to a bank account specified by Lee 8 the full amount due to Lee 8 under the statements render by Lee 8 on or before the twentieth (20th) Day of the Issuing Month. If the Day for payment should fall upon a weekend or legal holiday, then such payment shall be made on the regular business Day immediately prior thereto. If Customer fails to pay such amounts when due, then interest shall accrue on all unpaid amounts from the date due until paid at a rate equal to the applicable quarterly interest rate published by the FERC.
12.3 Billing Adjustments. In the event that Customer disputes any portion of a statement rendered pursuant to this Section 12, the total undisputed amount shall nevertheless be paid when due. If the parties cannot resolve the dispute within 15 days after such payment, the matter shall be submitted to a mutually agreed upon firm or nationally known public accountants or other third party with appropriate expertise (the “Expert”) who shall examine the records and billings and make a written report thereon, which shall be delivered to each party. The decision rendered by the Expert in this report shall be binding upon both parties. The fees and expenses of the Expert incurred in connection with such determination shall be paid by the party against whom the decision is rendered. However, if both parties prevail with respect to some part of the Expert’s determination, the fees and expenses of the Expert shall be allocated among the parties in a manner appropriate to the Expert's determination. Each party shall pay for its own expenses, including attorney fees, with respect to any such dispute.
Should Customer fail to pay the undisputed amount of any statement rendered by Lee 8 when such amount is due, or should it fail to pay a disputed amount determined to be due pursuant to this Section 12. Customer shall pay Lee 8 interest on such amount at a rate equal to the prime the applicable quarterly interest rate published by the FERC. In addition Lee 8 may, upon 30 days prior written notice, and in addition to any other remedies it may have, suspend its performance under the Contract until such amount is paid, terminate the Contract, or suspend its performance and subsequently terminate this Contract.
If Customer shall find at any time within 24 months after the date of any statement rendered by Lee 8 that it has been overcharged, and if the overcharge shall have been paid, and Customer shall have made a claim therefore within 60 days of the date of discovery, the overcharge, if verified by Lee 8, shall be refunded by Lee 8 within 30 days after receipt to the claim.

15.2 Force Majeure. The term “force majeure” employed herein shall mean acts of God, strikes, lockouts or other industrial disturbances, explosions, act of a public enemy, wars, blockades, insurrections, riots, epidemics, temporary failure of gas supply, the binding order of any court or governmental authority which has been resisted in good faith by all reasonable legal means, unscheduled shutdowns (for purposes of necessary maintenance, repairs, alterations, relocation or construction of wells, machinery, lines of pipe or other facilities), breakage or accident to wells, machinery or lines of pipe, testing (as required by governmental authority or as deemed necessary by Lee 8 for the safe operation of the storage fields and related facilities), inability to obtain necessary material or supplies or permits or land rights, failure of wells surface equipment or pipelines, well or line freeze ups or any other cause, whether of the kind herein enumerated, or otherwise, not reasonable in the control of the party claiming suspension and which by the exercise of due diligence such party is unable to prevent or overcome. A failure to settle or prevent any strike or other industrial disturbance shall not be considered to be a matter within the control of the party claiming force majeure.
15.1 Lack of Performance.
